  /* Definitions of auxiliary maps for storing materialized views. */
  struct ATOMMETA_entry {
    long ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID; long ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID; STRING_TYPE ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE; STRING_TYPE ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME; long ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID; STRING_TYPE ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME; STRING_TYPE ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME; long __av;  ATOMMETA_entry* nxt; ATOMMETA_entry* prv;
    explicit ATOMMETA_entry() : nxt(nullptr), prv(nullptr) { /*ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID = 0L; ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID = 0L; ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE = ""; ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME = ""; ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID = 0L; ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME = ""; ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME = ""; __av = 0L; */ }
    explicit ATOMMETA_entry(const long c0, const long c1, const STRING_TYPE& c2, const STRING_TYPE& c3, const long c4, const STRING_TYPE& c5, const STRING_TYPE& c6, const long c7) { ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID = c0; ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID = c1; ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE = c2; ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME = c3; ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID = c4; ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME = c5; ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME = c6; __av = c7; }
    ATOMMETA_entry(const ATOMMETA_entry& other) : ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID( other.ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID ), ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID( other.ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID ), ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE( other.ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE ), ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME( other.ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME ), ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID( other.ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID ), ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME( other.ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME ), ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME( other.ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME ), __av( other.__av ), nxt( nullptr ), prv( nullptr ) {}
    FORCE_INLINE ATOMMETA_entry& modify(const long c0, const long c1, const STRING_TYPE& c2, const STRING_TYPE& c3, const long c4, const STRING_TYPE& c5, const STRING_TYPE& c6) { ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID = c0; ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID = c1; ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE = c2; ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME = c3; ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID = c4; ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME = c5; ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME = c6;  return *this; }
    FORCE_INLINE ATOMMETA_entry& modify1(const long c1) { ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID = c1;  return *this; }
    template<class Archive>
    void serialize(Archive& ar, const unsigned int version) const 
    {
      ar << ELEM_SEPARATOR;
      DBT_SERIALIZATION_NVP(ar, ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID);
      ar << ELEM_SEPARATOR;
      DBT_SERIALIZATION_NVP(ar, ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID);
      ar << ELEM_SEPARATOR;
      DBT_SERIALIZATION_NVP(ar, ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE);
      ar << ELEM_SEPARATOR;
      DBT_SERIALIZATION_NVP(ar, ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME);
      ar << ELEM_SEPARATOR;
      DBT_SERIALIZATION_NVP(ar, ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID);
      ar << ELEM_SEPARATOR;
      DBT_SERIALIZATION_NVP(ar, ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME);
      ar << ELEM_SEPARATOR;
      DBT_SERIALIZATION_NVP(ar, ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME);
      ar << ELEM_SEPARATOR;
      DBT_SERIALIZATION_NVP(ar, __av);
    }
  };
  struct ATOMMETA_mapkey0123456_idxfn {
    FORCE_INLINE static size_t hash(const ATOMMETA_entry& e) {
      size_t h = 0;
      hash_combine(h, e.ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID);
      hash_combine(h, e.ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID);
      hash_combine(h, e.ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE);
      hash_combine(h, e.ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME);
      hash_combine(h, e.ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID);
      hash_combine(h, e.ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME);
      hash_combine(h, e.ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME);
      return h;
    }
    FORCE_INLINE static bool equals(const ATOMMETA_entry& x, const ATOMMETA_entry& y) {
      return x.ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID == y.ATOMMETA_PROTEIN_ID && x.ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID == y.ATOMMETA_ATOM_ID && x.ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE == y.ATOMMETA_ATOM_TYPE && x.ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME == y.ATOMMETA_ATOM_NAME && x.ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID == y.ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_ID && x.ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME == y.ATOMMETA_RESIDUE_NAME && x.ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME == y.ATOMMETA_SEGMENT_NAME;
    }
  };

  /* Type definition providing a way to access the results of the sql program */
  struct tlq_t{
    struct timeval t0,t; long tT,tN,tS;
    tlq_t(): tN(0), tS(0) { gettimeofday(&t0,NULL); }
  
  /* Serialization Code */
    template<class Archive>
    void serialize(Archive& ar, const unsigned int version) const {
  
      ar << "\n";
      const COUNT_map& _COUNT = get_COUNT();
      dbtoaster::serialize_nvp_tabbed(ar, STRING(COUNT), _COUNT, "\t");
  
    }
  
    /* Functions returning / computing the results of top level queries */
    const COUNT_map& get_COUNT() const {
      return COUNT;
    
    }
  
  protected:
  
    /* Data structures used for storing / computing top level queries */
    COUNT_map COUNT;
  
  };
  
  /* Type definition providing a way to incrementally maintain the results of the sql program */

  /* Type definition providing a way to execute the sql program */
  class Program : public ProgramBase
  {
    public:
      Program(int argc = 0, char* argv[] = 0) : ProgramBase(argc,argv) {
        data.register_data(*this);
        
        /* Specifying data sources */
        
        pair<string,string> source1_adaptor_params[] = { make_pair("schema","long,long,string,string,long,string,string") };
        std::shared_ptr<csv_adaptor> source1_adaptor(new csv_adaptor(get_relation_id("ATOMMETA"),1,source1_adaptor_params));
        frame_descriptor source1_fd("\n");
        std::shared_ptr<dbt_file_source> source1_file(new dbt_file_source("/Users/dashti/Documents/MyWorkspaces/DATASRC/dbtoaster/experiments/data/mddb/standard/atommeta.csv",source1_fd,source1_adaptor));
        add_source(source1_file, true);
        
        pair<string,string> source2_adaptor_params[] = { make_pair("schema","long,long,long,long,long,double,double,double") };
        std::shared_ptr<csv_adaptor> source2_adaptor(new csv_adaptor(get_relation_id("DIHEDRALS"),1,source2_adaptor_params));
        frame_descriptor source2_fd("\n");
        std::shared_ptr<dbt_file_source> source2_file(new dbt_file_source("/Users/dashti/Documents/MyWorkspaces/DATASRC/dbtoaster/experiments/data/mddb/standard/dihedrals.csv",source2_fd,source2_adaptor));
        add_source(source2_file, true);
        
        pair<string,string> source3_adaptor_params[] = { make_pair("schema","long,long,long,long,long") };
        std::shared_ptr<csv_adaptor> source3_adaptor(new csv_adaptor(get_relation_id("DIMENSIONS"),1,source3_adaptor_params));
        frame_descriptor source3_fd("\n");
        std::shared_ptr<dbt_file_source> source3_file(new dbt_file_source("/Users/dashti/Documents/MyWorkspaces/DATASRC/dbtoaster/experiments/data/mddb/standard/dimensions.csv",source3_fd,source3_adaptor));
        add_source(source3_file, true);
        
        pair<string,string> source4_adaptor_params[] = { make_pair("schema","long,long,long,double,double,double") };
        std::shared_ptr<csv_adaptor> source4_adaptor(new csv_adaptor(get_relation_id("ATOMPOSITIONS"),1,source4_adaptor_params));
        frame_descriptor source4_fd("\n");
        std::shared_ptr<dbt_file_source> source4_file(new dbt_file_source("/Users/dashti/Documents/MyWorkspaces/DATASRC/dbtoaster/experiments/data/mddb/standard/atompositions.csv",source4_fd,source4_adaptor));
        add_source(source4_file);
  
      }
  
      /* Imports data for static tables and performs view initialization based on it. */
      void init() {
          //P0_PLACE_HOLDER
          table_multiplexer.init_source(run_opts->batch_size, run_opts->parallel, true);
          stream_multiplexer.init_source(run_opts->batch_size, run_opts->parallel, false);
          process_tables();
          data.on_system_ready_event();
          //P2_PLACE_HOLDER
      }
  
      /* Saves a snapshot of the data required to obtain the results of top level queries. */
      snapshot_t take_snapshot(){
          tlq_t* d = new tlq_t((tlq_t&)data);
          if (d->tS==0) { gettimeofday(&(d->t),NULL); d->tT=((d->t).tv_sec-(d->t0).tv_sec)*1000000L+((d->t).tv_usec-(d->t0).tv_usec); } printf("SAMPLE=standard,%ld,%ld,%ld\n",d->tT,d->tN,d->tS);
          return snapshot_t( d );
      }
  
    protected:
      data_t data;
  };
  class Mddb2 : public Program
  {
    public:
      Mddb2(int argc = 0, char* argv[] = 0) : Program(argc,argv) {
      }
  };
